<subSubSection id="C3776556EDD538B1FC9AFF63FBBCFF28" pageId="644" pageNumber="645" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BD236DDEDD538B1FC9AFF63FBBCFF28" blockId="644.[810,1452,173,1288]" pageId="644" pageNumber="645">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEDD538B1FC9AFF63FC25FF06" bold="true" box="[863,992,173,199]" pageId="644" pageNumber="645">Etymology</emphasis>
. The specific name refers to the presence of four setae on the mandible.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3776556EDD538B1FC9AFF3FFBE5FC36" pageId="644" pageNumber="645" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BD236DDEDD538B1FC9AFF3FFAB7FE38" blockId="644.[810,1452,173,1288]" pageId="644" pageNumber="645">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEDD538B1FC9AFF3FFB9CFECA" bold="true" box="[863,1113,241,267]" pageId="644" pageNumber="645">Descriptionoffemale</emphasis>
. Body (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EDD538B1FB6BFF3FFAE5FECA" box="[1198,1312,241,267]" captionStart="FIGURE 438" captionStartId="645.[136,245,1567,1593]" captionTargetBox="[182,1410,213,1486]" captionTargetId="figure-135@645.[136,1451,182,1525]" captionTargetPageId="645" captionText="FIGURE 438. Nodoscarus quadrisetatus gen. et sp. nov., female. A, habitus, ventral; B, posterior end of body, ventral; C, cephalic region, ventral; D, antenna; E, mandible; F, maxillule. Scale bars: A, 1 mm; B, 0.1 mm; C, 0.05 mm; D–F, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592196" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592196/files/figure.png" pageId="644" pageNumber="645">Fig. 438A</figureCitation>
) vermiform, elongate, cylindrical, unsegmented, almost straight, surface densely covered with fine setules (setules not shown in 
<figureCitation id="13562A58EDD538B1FC57FE99FBE7FEB0" box="[914,1058,343,369]" captionStart="FIGURE 438" captionStartId="645.[136,245,1567,1593]" captionTargetBox="[182,1410,213,1486]" captionTargetId="figure-135@645.[136,1451,182,1525]" captionTargetPageId="645" captionText="FIGURE 438. Nodoscarus quadrisetatus gen. et sp. nov., female. A, habitus, ventral; B, posterior end of body, ventral; C, cephalic region, ventral; D, antenna; E, mandible; F, maxillule. Scale bars: A, 1 mm; B, 0.1 mm; C, 0.05 mm; D–F, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592196" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592196/files/figure.png" pageId="644" pageNumber="645">Fig. 438A, B</figureCitation>
). Bodylength 6.25 mm; body width 0.93 mm in middle. Paired convoluted ovaries, occupying 70% of body length, visible through body wall. Body tapering slightly anteriorly. Posterior end of body (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EDD538B1FABBFE73FCADFE38" captionStart="FIGURE 438" captionStartId="645.[136,245,1567,1593]" captionTargetBox="[182,1410,213,1486]" captionTargetId="figure-135@645.[136,1451,182,1525]" captionTargetPageId="645" captionText="FIGURE 438. Nodoscarus quadrisetatus gen. et sp. nov., female. A, habitus, ventral; B, posterior end of body, ventral; C, cephalic region, ventral; D, antenna; E, mandible; F, maxillule. Scale bars: A, 1 mm; B, 0.1 mm; C, 0.05 mm; D–F, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592196" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592196/files/figure.png" pageId="644" pageNumber="645">Fig. 438B</figureCitation>
) bilobed, with shallow median (anal) incision.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD236DDEDD538B1FC9AFDCCFC2CFCC8" blockId="644.[810,1452,173,1288]" pageId="644" pageNumber="645">
Rostrum absent (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EDD538B1FBE5FDCFFB52FDDA" box="[1056,1175,513,539]" captionStart="FIGURE 438" captionStartId="645.[136,245,1567,1593]" captionTargetBox="[182,1410,213,1486]" captionTargetId="figure-135@645.[136,1451,182,1525]" captionTargetPageId="645" captionText="FIGURE 438. Nodoscarus quadrisetatus gen. et sp. nov., female. A, habitus, ventral; B, posterior end of body, ventral; C, cephalic region, ventral; D, antenna; E, mandible; F, maxillule. Scale bars: A, 1 mm; B, 0.1 mm; C, 0.05 mm; D–F, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592196" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592196/files/figure.png" pageId="644" pageNumber="645">Fig. 438C</figureCitation>
). Antennule (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EDD538B1FAF5FDCFFA66FDDA" box="[1328,1443,513,539]" captionStart="FIGURE 438" captionStartId="645.[136,245,1567,1593]" captionTargetBox="[182,1410,213,1486]" captionTargetId="figure-135@645.[136,1451,182,1525]" captionTargetPageId="645" captionText="FIGURE 438. Nodoscarus quadrisetatus gen. et sp. nov., female. A, habitus, ventral; B, posterior end of body, ventral; C, cephalic region, ventral; D, antenna; E, mandible; F, maxillule. Scale bars: A, 1 mm; B, 0.1 mm; C, 0.05 mm; D–F, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592196" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592196/files/figure.png" pageId="644" pageNumber="645">Fig. 438C</figureCitation>
) as broad, semicircular lobe, surface covered with fine setules plus 1 or 2 small setae apically. Antenna (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EDD538B1FABBFD8BFCACFD40" captionStart="FIGURE 438" captionStartId="645.[136,245,1567,1593]" captionTargetBox="[182,1410,213,1486]" captionTargetId="figure-135@645.[136,1451,182,1525]" captionTargetPageId="645" captionText="FIGURE 438. Nodoscarus quadrisetatus gen. et sp. nov., female. A, habitus, ventral; B, posterior end of body, ventral; C, cephalic region, ventral; D, antenna; E, mandible; F, maxillule. Scale bars: A, 1 mm; B, 0.1 mm; C, 0.05 mm; D–F, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592196" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592196/files/figure.png" pageId="644" pageNumber="645">Fig. 438D</figureCitation>
) stout, 3-segmented: coxa short; basis only slightly longerthan wide, unarmed; endopod about 1.4 times longer than wide (24×17 μm): armed with 1 subdistal and 3 small distal setae, plus short, stout terminal claw, half as long as endopod.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD236DDEDD538B1FC9AFCDFFAAAFC14" blockId="644.[810,1452,173,1288]" pageId="644" pageNumber="645">
Labrum not discernible. Only 2 pairs of mouthparts present. Mandible (first pair, 
<figureCitation id="13562A58EDD538B1FB40FCFDFB3EFC8C" box="[1157,1275,819,845]" captionStart="FIGURE 438" captionStartId="645.[136,245,1567,1593]" captionTargetBox="[182,1410,213,1486]" captionTargetId="figure-135@645.[136,1451,182,1525]" captionTargetPageId="645" captionText="FIGURE 438. Nodoscarus quadrisetatus gen. et sp. nov., female. A, habitus, ventral; B, posterior end of body, ventral; C, cephalic region, ventral; D, antenna; E, mandible; F, maxillule. Scale bars: A, 1 mm; B, 0.1 mm; C, 0.05 mm; D–F, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592196" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592196/files/figure.png" pageId="644" pageNumber="645">Fig. 438E</figureCitation>
) lobate, tipped with 4 naked setae. Maxillule (second pair, 
<figureCitation id="13562A58EDD538B1FAF4FC9BFA61FCAE" box="[1329,1444,853,879]" captionStart="FIGURE 438" captionStartId="645.[136,245,1567,1593]" captionTargetBox="[182,1410,213,1486]" captionTargetId="figure-135@645.[136,1451,182,1525]" captionTargetPageId="645" captionText="FIGURE 438. Nodoscarus quadrisetatus gen. et sp. nov., female. A, habitus, ventral; B, posterior end of body, ventral; C, cephalic region, ventral; D, antenna; E, mandible; F, maxillule. Scale bars: A, 1 mm; B, 0.1 mm; C, 0.05 mm; D–F, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592196" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592196/files/figure.png" pageId="644" pageNumber="645">Fig. 438F</figureCitation>
) lobate, tipped with 2 setae. Large, anteriorly-directed, post-oral protuberance present posterior to oral region (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EDD538B1FCF7FC75FC62FC14" box="[818,935,955,981]" captionStart="FIGURE 438" captionStartId="645.[136,245,1567,1593]" captionTargetBox="[182,1410,213,1486]" captionTargetId="figure-135@645.[136,1451,182,1525]" captionTargetPageId="645" captionText="FIGURE 438. Nodoscarus quadrisetatus gen. et sp. nov., female. A, habitus, ventral; B, posterior end of body, ventral; C, cephalic region, ventral; D, antenna; E, mandible; F, maxillule. Scale bars: A, 1 mm; B, 0.1 mm; C, 0.05 mm; D–F, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592196" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592196/files/figure.png" pageId="644" pageNumber="645">Fig. 438C</figureCitation>
). Maxillae, maxillipeds, and legs absent.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD236DDEDD538B1FC9AFC13FBE5FC36" blockId="644.[810,1452,173,1288]" box="[863,1056,989,1016]" pageId="644" pageNumber="645">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEDD538B1FC9AFC13FC59FC36" bold="true" box="[863,924,989,1015]" pageId="644" pageNumber="645">Male</emphasis>
. Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3776556EDD538B1FC9AFC31FA5EFAC9" pageId="644" pageNumber="645" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BD236DDEDD538B1FC9AFC31FA5EFAC9" blockId="644.[810,1452,173,1288]" pageId="644" pageNumber="645">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEDD538B1FC9AFC31FC09FBD8" bold="true" box="[863,972,1023,1049]" pageId="644" pageNumber="645">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EEDD538B1FC26FC31FAD4FBD8" authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2020" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[995,1297,1023,1049]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Nodoscarus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="644" pageNumber="645" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadrisetatus" status="gen. et sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEDD538B1FC26FC31FAD4FBD8" box="[995,1297,1023,1049]" italics="true" pageId="644" pageNumber="645">Nodoscarus quadrisetatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B919EACFEDD538B1FAE7FC31FC9EFBFA" bold="true" pageId="644" pageNumber="645">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22A57B4EDD538B1FAE7FC31FC9EFBFA" pageId="644" pageNumber="645" rank="species">gen. et sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is best compared with 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EEDD538B1FBBEFBECFAD8FBFA" authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2020" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[1147,1309,1058,1084]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Nodoscarus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="644" pageNumber="645" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="senisetatus" status="gen. et sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEDD538B1FBBEFBECFB4BFBFA" box="[1147,1166,1058,1083]" italics="true" pageId="644" pageNumber="645">N</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B919EACFEDD538B1FB67FBECFAD8FBFA" box="[1186,1309,1058,1083]" italics="true" pageId="644" pageNumber="645">senisetatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B919EACFEDD538B1FAECFBEFFC9EFB9C" bold="true" pageId="644" pageNumber="645">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22A57B4EDD538B1FAECFBEFFC9EFB9C" pageId="644" pageNumber="645" rank="species">gen. et sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, because both of these two species retain only two pairs of mouthparts and share the presence of 2 setae on the second pair (the maxillules). The new species can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EEDD538B1FBC3FB64FB66FB02" authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2020" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[1030,1187,1194,1220]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Nodoscarus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="644" pageNumber="645" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="senisetatus" status="gen. et sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEDD538B1FBC3FB64FBDCFB02" box="[1030,1049,1194,1219]" italics="true" pageId="644" pageNumber="645">N</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B919EACFEDD538B1FBEDFB64FB66FB02" box="[1064,1187,1194,1219]" italics="true" pageId="644" pageNumber="645">senisetatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B919EACFEDD538B1FB6EFB67FA98FB02" bold="true" box="[1195,1373,1193,1219]" pageId="644" pageNumber="645">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22A57B4EDD538B1FB6EFB67FA98FB02" box="[1195,1373,1193,1219]" pageId="644" pageNumber="645" rank="species">gen. et sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
by the lack of a rostrum and by the possession of 4 setae on the mandible (vs. 6 setaein 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EEDD538B1FBFFFB20FB13FAC6" authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2020" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[1082,1238,1262,1288]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Nodoscarus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="644" pageNumber="645" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="senisetatus" status="gen. et sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEDD538B1FBFFFB20FB88FAC6" box="[1082,1101,1262,1287]" italics="true" pageId="644" pageNumber="645">N</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B919EACFEDD538B1FB9EFB20FB13FAC6" box="[1115,1238,1262,1287]" italics="true" pageId="644" pageNumber="645">senisetatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B919EACFEDD538B1FB19FB23FA4EFAC6" bold="true" box="[1244,1419,1261,1287]" pageId="644" pageNumber="645">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22A57B4EDD538B1FB19FB23FA4EFAC6" box="[1244,1419,1261,1287]" pageId="644" pageNumber="645" rank="species">gen. etsp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
).
</paragraph>
